#: ../../A/awk.rst:9
msgid ""
"n\\. [Unix techspeak] An interpreted language for massaging text data "
"developed by Alfred Aho, Peter Weinberger, and Brian Kernighan (the name "
"derives from their initials). It is characterized by C-like syntax, a "
"declaration-free approach to variable typing and declarations, associative "
"arrays, and field-oriented text processing. See also :ref:`Perl`\\."
msgstr ""
"名詞。[Unix専門用語]Alfred Aho、Peter Weinberger、Brian "
"Kernighanが開発した、テキストデータを加工するためのインタプリタ言語(名前は彼らのイニシャルに由来する)。C風の構文、変数の型付けや宣言を不要とする方式、連想配列、フィールド指向のテキスト処理を特徴とする。\\"
" :ref:`Perl`\\ も参照。"

#: ../../A/awk.rst:14
msgid ""
"n\\. Editing term for an expression awkward to manipulate through normal "
":ref:`regexp` facilities (for example, one containing a :ref:`newline`\\)."
msgstr ""
"名詞。通常の\\ :ref:`regexp`\\ 機能では扱いにくい(awkwardな)式を指す編集用語(たとえば\\ :ref:`newline`\\"
" を含むもの)。"

#: ../../A/awk.rst:17
msgid "vt\\. To process data using :manpage:`awk(1)`\\."
msgstr "他動詞。\\ :manpage:`awk(1)`\\ を使ってデータを処理すること。"
